## Requirements

You'll need the following to get started.

- <%= Suspenders::RUBY_VERSION %>
- Postgres
- Heroku CLI
- [Mailcatcher](https://mailcatcher.me/)

## Getting Started

To get started, simply run `bin/setup`. This will do the following:

- Setup git remotes for the kohactive upstream and Heroku production
- Bundle install
- Copy the .env.example over to .env
- Setup the database
- Clear any logs or temporary files

Once the setup is complete, you can modify any environment variables in the `.env` file, if needed.

After setting up, you can run the application using [Heroku Local]:

    % heroku local

[Heroku Local]: https://devcenter.heroku.com/articles/heroku-local

